<!--    Type scale
        https://m2.material.io/design/typography/the-type-system.html#type-scale

        give the style a name which will referred to in the textview
        The parent specifies which type of text view. The Headlines have semantic meaning, so choose them appropriately,
        (is the element the main heading - use H1 etc. this is for screen readers and accessibility)
         but you can change the fontSize here or override if need be

         more guidelines: Mobile Text guidelines https://www.learnui.design/blog/android-material-design-font-size-guidelines.html

-->
    <style name="TextAppearance.myH1_serif" parent="TextAppearance.MaterialComponents.Headline1">
        <item name="fontFamily">@font/playfair_display</item>
        <item name="android:fontFamily">@font/playfair_display</item>
        <item name="android:textSize">22sp</item>
    </style>
